File: eNCA has parted company with its Director of News Kanthan Pillay with immediate effect. JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Editors Forum (Sanef) welcomed eNCA's dismissal of Kanthan Pillay. Sanef says it's unacceptable that a politician was ever allowed to become the channel's Director of News and wants management to explain how it happened. Pillay is the leader of the Capitalist Party who contested this year's national elections. READ: eNCA and Kanthan Pillay part company eNCA announced his dismissal after one of his tweets sparked outrage on social media. The channel says it will appoint an external expert to investigate allegations that Pillay censored stories and has agreed to cooperate with Sanef.